I am not a huge wrestling fan, but have always had at least a background interest in it. And watching the occasional ppv when my friend orders it has kept me slightly up to date. 
After the recent women's Royal Rumble and women's Hell in the Cell, I've had a recurring conversation with my friends, my brother, co workers, etc. It is just so fucking awesome that women are finally getting real matches! That they're allowed to actually freaking wrestle!

Now like any other red blooded guy out there, we'll sit there and talk about how hot this or that superstar is, but that's all taken a back seat now. For years we would play wrestling games and be pissed that any custom female character we created could only compete in women's events, and those women's events only had like 3 options. They weren't wrestlers, they were "divas". They were just overly made up reality star wannabes who'd get in the ring, look pretty for a bit, and that was basically it. 

Now we got some real women who can really fucking wrestle! We got more than girls who are just eye candy. When Nia Jax got into the rumble and just wrecked house, it was awesome! (Sorry if anyone is offended that I don't think Nia is the hottest girl out there, but that's just the point. It's not important.)
I don't know why they thought wrestling fans weren't interested in the female wrestlers. Why they thought they had to be a token addition instead of actual superstars who could put on a show. Thank god that seems to be changing.
